<p>I'm trying to set a Knockout-bound function's parameter with Razor. I've tried...</p>  <pre><code>&lt;a href="#" data-bind="click: function() { return myFunc(@Type.SomeType.ToString()); }"&gt;     Click Me &lt;/a&gt; </code></pre>  <p>and..</p>  <pre><code>&lt;a href="#" data-bind="click: function() { return myFunc(@Html.Raw(Type.SomeType.ToString())); }"&gt;     Click Me &lt;/a&gt; </code></pre>  <p>and..</p>  <pre><code>&lt;a href="#" data-bind="click: function() { return myFunc('@Html.Raw(Type.SomeType.ToString())'); }"&gt;     Click Me &lt;/a&gt; </code></pre>  <p>and..</p>  <pre><code>&lt;a href="#" data-bind="click: function() { return myFunc('@(Html.Raw(Type.SomeType.ToString()))'); }"&gt;     Click Me &lt;/a&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Is there a right way to do this? </p>  <p>(Background: this is for use in a bootstrap dropdown)</p>